Note: Runa Standard Library - Post-Quantum Cryptography
This module provides production-grade post-quantum cryptographic algorithms resistant
to quantum computer attacks, including NIST PQC winners: CRYSTALS-Kyber, CRYSTALS-Dilithium,
FALCON, and SPHINCS+, plus lattice-based and code-based alternatives.

Supports key encapsulation mechanisms (KEM), digital signatures, and hybrid classical/PQC
schemes for quantum-safe cryptographic transitions.

Specification compliance: NIST PQC Standards, RFC drafts for PQC algorithms, FIPS 203/204/205.
:End Note

Import "crypto/asymmetric" as asymmetric
Import "crypto/hash" as hash
Import "crypto/primitives/random" as random
Import "crypto/primitives/polynomial" as poly
Import "crypto/primitives/lattice" as lattice

Type PqcKeyPair is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as String
    security_level as Integer
    public_key as PqcPublicKey
    private_key as PqcPrivateKey
    key_size_bits as Integer
    generation_params as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type PqcPublicKey is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as String
    key_bytes as List[Integer]
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    security_level as Integer
    key_usage as List[String]

Type PqcPrivateKey is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as String
    key_bytes as List[Integer]
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    security_level as Integer
    key_usage as List[String]

Type PqcSignature is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as String
    signature_bytes as List[Integer]
    security_level as Integer
    signature_scheme as String
    randomness_used as List[Integer]

Type PqcCiphertextResult is Dictionary with:
    ciphertext as List[Integer]
    shared_secret as List[Integer]
    encapsulation_algorithm as String
    security_level as Integer

Type PqcHybridKey is Dictionary with:
    classical_component as asymmetric.AsymmetricKeyPair
    pqc_component as PqcKeyPair
    combination_method as String
    security_policy as String

Type PqcResult is Union with:
    PqcSuccess with value as Dictionary[String, Any]
    PqcFailure with error as PqcError and message as String

Type PqcError is Enum with:
    Invalid_Algorithm
    Invalid_Key
    Invalid_Signature
    Invalid_Parameters
    Key_Generation_Failed
    Signature_Failed
    Verification_Failed
    Encapsulation_Failed
    Decapsulation_Failed
    Unsupported_Security_Level
    Quantum_Vulnerability_Detected
    Internal_Error

Note: NIST PQC Algorithm Constants
Let KYBER_512 be "CRYSTALS-Kyber-512"
Let KYBER_768 be "CRYSTALS-Kyber-768"
Let KYBER_1024 be "CRYSTALS-Kyber-1024"
Let DILITHIUM_2 be "CRYSTALS-Dilithium-2"
Let DILITHIUM_3 be "CRYSTALS-Dilithium-3"
Let DILITHIUM_5 be "CRYSTALS-Dilithium-5"
Let FALCON_512 be "FALCON-512"
Let FALCON_1024 be "FALCON-1024"
Let SPHINCS_SHA256_128S be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-128s"
Let SPHINCS_SHA256_128F be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-128f"
Let SPHINCS_SHA256_192S be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-192s"
Let SPHINCS_SHA256_192F be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-192f"
Let SPHINCS_SHA256_256S be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-256s"
Let SPHINCS_SHA256_256F be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-256f"

Note: Alternative PQC Algorithms
Let NTRU_HPS_2048_509 be "NTRU-HPS-2048-509"
Let NTRU_HPS_2048_677 be "NTRU-HPS-2048-677"
Let NTRU_HRSS_701 be "NTRU-HRSS-701"
Let SABER_LIGHTSABER be "Saber-LightSaber"
Let SABER_SABER be "Saber-Saber"
Let SABER_FIRESABER be "Saber-FireSaber"
Let MCELIECE_348864 be "Classic-McEliece-348864"
Let MCELIECE_460896 be "Classic-McEliece-460896"
Let MCELIECE_6688128 be "Classic-McEliece-6688128"

Note: Security Levels (NIST Categories)
Let SECURITY_LEVEL_1 be 1  Note: Equivalent to AES-128
Let SECURITY_LEVEL_3 be 3  Note: Equivalent to AES-192  
Let SECURITY_LEVEL_5 be 5  Note: Equivalent to AES-256

Note: Key Usage Types
Let USAGE_KEM be "key_encapsulation"
Let USAGE_SIGNATURE be "digital_signature"
Let USAGE_HYBRID be "hybrid_classical_pqc"

Note: Primary PQC Interface Functions

Process called "generate_pqc_keypair" that takes algorithm as String and security_level as Integer and parameters as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns PqcResult[PqcKeyPair]:
    Note: Generate post-quantum cryptographic key pair
    Try:
        Note: Validate algorithm and security level
        Let validation_result be validate_pqc_parameters with algorithm as algorithm and security_level as security_level and parameters as parameters
        Match validation_result:
            When PqcFailure:
                Return validation_result
            When PqcSuccess with value as validated_params:
                Note: Generate key pair based on algorithm family
                Match algorithm:
                    When KYBER_512:
                        Return generate_kyber_keypair with security_level as 1 and params as validated_params
                    When KYBER_768:
                        Return generate_kyber_keypair with security_level as 3 and params as validated_params
                    When KYBER_1024:
                        Return generate_kyber_keypair with security_level as 5 and params as validated_params
                    When DILITHIUM_2:
                        Return generate_dilithium_keypair with security_level as 1 and params as validated_params
                    When DILITHIUM_3:
                        Return generate_dilithium_keypair with security_level as 3 and params as validated_params
                    When DILITHIUM_5:
                        Return generate_dilithium_keypair with security_level as 5 and params as validated_params
                    When FALCON_512:
                        Return generate_falcon_keypair with security_level as 1 and params as validated_params
                    When FALCON_1024:
                        Return generate_falcon_keypair with security_level as 5 and params as validated_params
                    When SPHINCS_SHA256_128S:
                        Return generate_sphincs_keypair with security_level as 1 and variant as "128s" and params as validated_params
                    When SPHINCS_SHA256_128F:
                        Return generate_sphincs_keypair with security_level as 1 and variant as "128f" and params as validated_params
                    When NTRU_HPS_2048_509:
                        Return generate_ntru_keypair with variant as "hps-2048-509" and params as validated_params
                    When MCELIECE_348864:
                        Return generate_mceliece_keypair with variant as "348864" and params as validated_params
                    Otherwise:
                        Return PqcFailure with:
                            error as PqcError.Invalid_Algorithm
                            message as "Unsupported PQC algorithm: " plus algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
            message as "PQC key generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "pqc_sign_message" that takes private_key as PqcPrivateKey and message as List[Integer] and context as Optional[String] returns PqcResult[PqcSignature]:
    Note: Create post-quantum digital signature
    Try:
        Note: Validate private key for signing
        If not ("digital_signature" is in private_key.key_usage):
            Return PqcFailure with:
                error as PqcError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Private key not authorized for digital signatures"
        
        Note: Perform algorithm-specific signing
        Match private_key.algorithm:
            When DILITHIUM_2:
                Return dilithium_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and security_level as 1
            When DILITHIUM_3:
                Return dilithium_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and security_level as 3
            When DILITHIUM_5:
                Return dilithium_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and security_level as 5
            When FALCON_512:
                Return falcon_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and security_level as 1
            When FALCON_1024:
                Return falcon_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and security_level as 5
            When SPHINCS_SHA256_128S:
                Return sphincs_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and variant as "128s" and context as context
            When SPHINCS_SHA256_128F:
                Return sphincs_sign with private_key as private_key and message as message and variant as "128f" and context as context
            Otherwise:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Invalid_Algorithm
                    message as "Algorithm does not support digital signatures: " plus private_key.algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Signature_Failed
            message as "PQC signature creation error: " plus error as String

Process called "pqc_verify_signature" that takes public_key as PqcPublicKey and message as List[Integer] and signature as PqcSignature and context as Optional[String] returns PqcResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Verify post-quantum digital signature
    Try:
        Note: Validate algorithm compatibility
        If public_key.algorithm is not equal to signature.algorithm:
            Return PqcFailure with:
                error as PqcError.Invalid_Signature
                message as "Key algorithm mismatch with signature algorithm"
        
        Note: Perform algorithm-specific verification
        Match public_key.algorithm:
            When DILITHIUM_2:
                Return dilithium_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and security_level as 1
            When DILITHIUM_3:
                Return dilithium_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and security_level as 3
            When DILITHIUM_5:
                Return dilithium_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and security_level as 5
            When FALCON_512:
                Return falcon_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and security_level as 1
            When FALCON_1024:
                Return falcon_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and security_level as 5
            When SPHINCS_SHA256_128S:
                Return sphincs_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and variant as "128s" and context as context
            When SPHINCS_SHA256_128F:
                Return sphincs_verify with public_key as public_key and message as message and signature as signature and variant as "128f" and context as context
            Otherwise:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Invalid_Algorithm
                    message as "Algorithm does not support signature verification: " plus public_key.algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Verification_Failed
            message as "PQC signature verification error: " plus error as String

Process called "pqc_encapsulate" that takes public_key as PqcPublicKey returns PqcResult[PqcCiphertextResult]:
    Note: Perform key encapsulation mechanism (KEM) to generate shared secret
    Try:
        Note: Validate public key for KEM
        If not ("key_encapsulation" is in public_key.key_usage):
            Return PqcFailure with:
                error as PqcError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Public key not authorized for key encapsulation"
        
        Note: Perform algorithm-specific encapsulation
        Match public_key.algorithm:
            When KYBER_512:
                Return kyber_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and security_level as 1
            When KYBER_768:
                Return kyber_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and security_level as 3
            When KYBER_1024:
                Return kyber_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and security_level as 5
            When NTRU_HPS_2048_509:
                Return ntru_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and variant as "hps-2048-509"
            When NTRU_HPS_2048_677:
                Return ntru_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and variant as "hps-2048-677"
            When SABER_LIGHTSABER:
                Return saber_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and variant as "lightsaber"
            When MCELIECE_348864:
                Return mceliece_encapsulate with public_key as public_key and variant as "348864"
            Otherwise:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Invalid_Algorithm
                    message as "Algorithm does not support key encapsulation: " plus public_key.algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Encapsulation_Failed
            message as "PQC encapsulation error: " plus error as String

Process called "pqc_decapsulate" that takes private_key as PqcPrivateKey and ciphertext as List[Integer] returns PqcResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Perform key decapsulation to recover shared secret
    Try:
        Note: Validate private key for KEM
        If not ("key_encapsulation" is in private_key.key_usage):
            Return PqcFailure with:
                error as PqcError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Private key not authorized for key decapsulation"
        
        Note: Perform algorithm-specific decapsulation
        Match private_key.algorithm:
            When KYBER_512:
                Return kyber_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and security_level as 1
            When KYBER_768:
                Return kyber_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and security_level as 3
            When KYBER_1024:
                Return kyber_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and security_level as 5
            When NTRU_HPS_2048_509:
                Return ntru_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and variant as "hps-2048-509"
            When NTRU_HPS_2048_677:
                Return ntru_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and variant as "hps-2048-677"
            When SABER_LIGHTSABER:
                Return saber_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and variant as "lightsaber"
            When MCELIECE_348864:
                Return mceliece_decapsulate with private_key as private_key and ciphertext as ciphertext and variant as "348864"
            Otherwise:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Invalid_Algorithm
                    message as "Algorithm does not support key decapsulation: " plus private_key.algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Decapsulation_Failed
            message as "PQC decapsulation error: " plus error as String

Process called "create_hybrid_keypair" that takes classical_algorithm as String and pqc_algorithm as String and security_level as Integer returns PqcResult[PqcHybridKey]:
    Note: Create hybrid classical/post-quantum key pair for transition security
    Try:
        Note: Generate classical key pair
        Let classical_result be asymmetric.generate_key_pair with algorithm as classical_algorithm and key_size as None
        Match classical_result:
            When asymmetric.AsymmetricFailure:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
                    message as "Classical key generation failed: " plus classical_result.message
            When asymmetric.AsymmetricSuccess with value as classical_keypair:
                Note: Generate PQC key pair
                Let pqc_result be generate_pqc_keypair with algorithm as pqc_algorithm and security_level as security_level and parameters as None
                Match pqc_result:
                    When PqcFailure:
                        Return pqc_result
                    When PqcSuccess with value as pqc_keypair:
                        Note: Determine combination method based on algorithms
                        Let combination_method be determine_hybrid_combination_method with classical_alg as classical_algorithm and pqc_alg as pqc_algorithm
                        
                        Let hybrid_key be PqcHybridKey with:
                            classical_component as classical_keypair
                            pqc_component as pqc_keypair
                            combination_method as combination_method
                            security_policy as "quantum_safe_transition"
                        
                        Return PqcSuccess with value as hybrid_key
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
            message as "Hybrid key generation error: " plus error as String

Note: CRYSTALS-Kyber Implementation (NIST PQC KEM Winner)

Process called "generate_kyber_keypair" that takes security_level as Integer and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PqcResult[PqcKeyPair]:
    Note: Generate CRYSTALS-Kyber key pair for key encapsulation
    Try:
        Note: Set parameters based on security level
        Let kyber_params be get_kyber_parameters with security_level as security_level
        
        Note: Generate random seed for key generation
        Let seed_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as 64
        Match seed_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
                    message as "Failed to generate Kyber seed"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as seed:
                Note: Generate public and private keys using Kyber algorithm
                Let keypair_result be kyber_generate_keys with seed as seed and params as kyber_params
                Match keypair_result:
                    When PqcSuccess with value as keys:
                        Let public_key be PqcPublicKey with:
                            algorithm as ("CRYSTALS-Kyber-" plus (kyber_params["k"] multiplied by 256) as String)
                            key_bytes as keys["public_key"]
                            parameters as kyber_params
                            security_level as security_level
                            key_usage as list containing USAGE_KEM
                        
                        Let private_key be PqcPrivateKey with:
                            algorithm as ("CRYSTALS-Kyber-" plus (kyber_params["k"] multiplied by 256) as String)
                            key_bytes as keys["private_key"]
                            parameters as kyber_params
                            security_level as security_level
                            key_usage as list containing USAGE_KEM
                        
                        Let keypair be PqcKeyPair with:
                            algorithm as ("CRYSTALS-Kyber-" plus (kyber_params["k"] multiplied by 256) as String)
                            security_level as security_level
                            public_key as public_key
                            private_key as private_key
                            key_size_bits as (kyber_params["n"] multiplied by kyber_params["k"] multiplied by kyber_params["q_bits"])
                            generation_params as kyber_params
                        
                        Return PqcSuccess with value as keypair
                    When PqcFailure:
                        Return keypair_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
            message as "Kyber key generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "kyber_encapsulate" that takes public_key as PqcPublicKey and security_level as Integer returns PqcResult[PqcCiphertextResult]:
    Note: Perform Kyber key encapsulation
    Try:
        Note: Generate random message to encapsulate
        Let message_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as 32
        Match message_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Encapsulation_Failed
                    message as "Failed to generate Kyber encapsulation message"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as message:
                Note: Perform Kyber encapsulation algorithm
                Let encap_result be kyber_encrypt with public_key_bytes as public_key.key_bytes and message as message and params as public_key.parameters
                Match encap_result:
                    When PqcSuccess with value as encap_data:
                        Note: Derive shared secret from message using KDF
                        Let shared_secret_result be hash.compute_hash with data as message and algorithm as "SHA256"
                        Match shared_secret_result:
                            When hash.HashSuccess with value as shared_secret:
                                Let ciphertext_result be PqcCiphertextResult with:
                                    ciphertext as encap_data["ciphertext"]
                                    shared_secret as shared_secret
                                    encapsulation_algorithm as public_key.algorithm
                                    security_level as security_level
                                
                                Return PqcSuccess with value as ciphertext_result
                            When hash.HashFailure:
                                Return PqcFailure with:
                                    error as PqcError.Encapsulation_Failed
                                    message as "Shared secret derivation failed"
                    When PqcFailure:
                        Return encap_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Encapsulation_Failed
            message as "Kyber encapsulation error: " plus error as String

Note: CRYSTALS-Dilithium Implementation (NIST PQC Signature Winner)

Process called "generate_dilithium_keypair" that takes security_level as Integer and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PqcResult[PqcKeyPair]:
    Note: Generate CRYSTALS-Dilithium key pair for digital signatures
    Try:
        Note: Set parameters based on security level
        Let dilithium_params be get_dilithium_parameters with security_level as security_level
        
        Note: Generate random seed for key generation
        Let seed_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as 32
        Match seed_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
                    message as "Failed to generate Dilithium seed"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as seed:
                Note: Generate keys using Dilithium algorithm
                Let keypair_result be dilithium_generate_keys with seed as seed and params as dilithium_params
                Match keypair_result:
                    When PqcSuccess with value as keys:
                        Let algorithm_name be "CRYSTALS-Dilithium-" plus security_level as String
                        
                        Let public_key be PqcPublicKey with:
                            algorithm as algorithm_name
                            key_bytes as keys["public_key"]
                            parameters as dilithium_params
                            security_level as security_level
                            key_usage as list containing USAGE_SIGNATURE
                        
                        Let private_key be PqcPrivateKey with:
                            algorithm as algorithm_name
                            key_bytes as keys["private_key"]
                            parameters as dilithium_params
                            security_level as security_level
                            key_usage as list containing USAGE_SIGNATURE
                        
                        Let keypair be PqcKeyPair with:
                            algorithm as algorithm_name
                            security_level as security_level
                            public_key as public_key
                            private_key as private_key
                            key_size_bits as (dilithium_params["n"] multiplied by (dilithium_params["k"] plus dilithium_params["l"]))
                            generation_params as dilithium_params
                        
                        Return PqcSuccess with value as keypair
                    When PqcFailure:
                        Return keypair_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
            message as "Dilithium key generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "dilithium_sign" that takes private_key as PqcPrivateKey and message as List[Integer] and security_level as Integer returns PqcResult[PqcSignature]:
    Note: Create Dilithium digital signature
    Try:
        Note: Hash message using SHAKE-256
        Let message_hash_result be hash.compute_hash with data as message and algorithm as "SHAKE256"
        Match message_hash_result:
            When hash.HashFailure:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Signature_Failed
                    message as "Message hashing failed: " plus message_hash_result.message
            When hash.HashSuccess with value as message_hash:
                Note: Generate randomness for signature
                Let randomness_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as 64
                Match randomness_result:
                    When random.RandomFailure:
                        Return PqcFailure with:
                            error as PqcError.Signature_Failed
                            message as "Failed to generate signature randomness"
                    When random.RandomSuccess with value as randomness:
                        Note: Perform Dilithium signing algorithm
                        Let signature_result be dilithium_sign_message with private_key_bytes as private_key.key_bytes and message_hash as message_hash and randomness as randomness and params as private_key.parameters
                        Match signature_result:
                            When PqcSuccess with value as sig_bytes:
                                Let signature be PqcSignature with:
                                    algorithm as private_key.algorithm
                                    signature_bytes as sig_bytes
                                    security_level as security_level
                                    signature_scheme as "Dilithium"
                                    randomness_used as randomness
                                
                                Return PqcSuccess with value as signature
                            When PqcFailure:
                                Return signature_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Signature_Failed
            message as "Dilithium signing error: " plus error as String

Note: FALCON Implementation (NIST PQC Signature Alternative)

Process called "generate_falcon_keypair" that takes security_level as Integer and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PqcResult[PqcKeyPair]:
    Note: Generate FALCON key pair for compact digital signatures
    Try:
        Note: Set FALCON parameters (n=512 for level 1, n=1024 for level 5)
        Let n be (if security_level is equal to 1: 512 else: 1024)
        Let falcon_params be dictionary containing:
            "n" as n,
            "q" as 12289,
            "sigma" as 1.17,
            "security_level" as security_level
        
        Note: Generate FALCON key pair using NTRU lattice
        Let keypair_result be falcon_generate_keys with params as falcon_params
        Match keypair_result:
            When PqcSuccess with value as keys:
                Let algorithm_name be "FALCON-" plus n as String
                
                Let public_key be PqcPublicKey with:
                    algorithm as algorithm_name
                    key_bytes as keys["public_key"]
                    parameters as falcon_params
                    security_level as security_level
                    key_usage as list containing USAGE_SIGNATURE
                
                Let private_key be PqcPrivateKey with:
                    algorithm as algorithm_name
                    key_bytes as keys["private_key"]
                    parameters as falcon_params
                    security_level as security_level
                    key_usage as list containing USAGE_SIGNATURE
                
                Let keypair be PqcKeyPair with:
                    algorithm as algorithm_name
                    security_level as security_level
                    public_key as public_key
                    private_key as private_key
                    key_size_bits as (n multiplied by 16)  Note: Approximate key size
                    generation_params as falcon_params
                
                Return PqcSuccess with value as keypair
            When PqcFailure:
                Return keypair_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
            message as "FALCON key generation error: " plus error as String

Note: SPHINCS+ Implementation (Hash-based Signatures)

Process called "generate_sphincs_keypair" that takes security_level as Integer and variant as String and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PqcResult[PqcKeyPair]:
    Note: Generate SPHINCS+ key pair for stateless hash-based signatures
    Try:
        Note: Set SPHINCS+ parameters based on security level and variant
        Let sphincs_params be get_sphincs_parameters with security_level as security_level and variant as variant
        
        Note: Generate random seed for SPHINCS+ key generation
        Let seed_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as sphincs_params["seed_length"]
        Match seed_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return PqcFailure with:
                    error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
                    message as "Failed to generate SPHINCS+ seed"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as seed:
                Note: Generate SPHINCS+ keys using Merkle trees and WOTS+
                Let keypair_result be sphincs_generate_keys with seed as seed and params as sphincs_params
                Match keypair_result:
                    When PqcSuccess with value as keys:
                        Let algorithm_name be "SPHINCS+-SHA256-" plus security_level as String plus variant
                        
                        Let public_key be PqcPublicKey with:
                            algorithm as algorithm_name
                            key_bytes as keys["public_key"]
                            parameters as sphincs_params
                            security_level as security_level
                            key_usage as list containing USAGE_SIGNATURE
                        
                        Let private_key be PqcPrivateKey with:
                            algorithm as algorithm_name
                            key_bytes as keys["private_key"]
                            parameters as sphincs_params
                            security_level as security_level
                            key_usage as list containing USAGE_SIGNATURE
                        
                        Let keypair be PqcKeyPair with:
                            algorithm as algorithm_name
                            security_level as security_level
                            public_key as public_key
                            private_key as private_key
                            key_size_bits as (sphincs_params["n"] multiplied by 8)
                            generation_params as sphincs_params
                        
                        Return PqcSuccess with value as keypair
                    When PqcFailure:
                        Return keypair_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Key_Generation_Failed
            message as "SPHINCS+ key generation error: " plus error as String

Note: Parameter Management and Utility Functions

Process called "get_kyber_parameters" that takes security_level as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get CRYSTALS-Kyber parameters for security level
    Match security_level:
        When 1:  Note: Kyber-512
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 2, "eta1" as 3, "eta2" as 2, "du" as 10, "dv" as 4, "n" as 256, "q" as 3329, "q_bits" as 12
        When 3:  Note: Kyber-768
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 3, "eta1" as 2, "eta2" as 2, "du" as 10, "dv" as 4, "n" as 256, "q" as 3329, "q_bits" as 12
        When 5:  Note: Kyber-1024
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 4, "eta1" as 2, "eta2" as 2, "du" as 11, "dv" as 5, "n" as 256, "q" as 3329, "q_bits" as 12
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 3, "eta1" as 2, "eta2" as 2, "du" as 10, "dv" as 4, "n" as 256, "q" as 3329, "q_bits" as 12

Process called "get_dilithium_parameters" that takes security_level as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get CRYSTALS-Dilithium parameters for security level
    Match security_level:
        When 1:  Note: Dilithium-2
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 4, "l" as 4, "eta" as 2, "tau" as 39, "beta" as 78, "gamma1" as 131072, "gamma2" as 95232, "omega" as 80, "n" as 256, "q" as 8380417
        When 3:  Note: Dilithium-3  
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 6, "l" as 5, "eta" as 4, "tau" as 49, "beta" as 196, "gamma1" as 524288, "gamma2" as 261888, "omega" as 55, "n" as 256, "q" as 8380417
        When 5:  Note: Dilithium-5
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 8, "l" as 7, "eta" as 2, "tau" as 60, "beta" as 120, "gamma1" as 524288, "gamma2" as 261888, "omega" as 75, "n" as 256, "q" as 8380417
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "k" as 6, "l" as 5, "eta" as 4, "tau" as 49, "beta" as 196, "gamma1" as 524288, "gamma2" as 261888, "omega" as 55, "n" as 256, "q" as 8380417

Process called "validate_pqc_parameters" that takes algorithm as String and security_level as Integer and parameters as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns PqcResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Validate PQC algorithm parameters
    Try:
        Note: Check if security level is supported
        If security_level is not in list containing 1, 3, 5:
            Return PqcFailure with:
                error as PqcError.Unsupported_Security_Level
                message as "Security level must be 1, 3, or 5"
        
        Note: Validate algorithm-specific constraints
        Let supported_algorithms be list containing KYBER_512, KYBER_768, KYBER_1024, DILITHIUM_2, DILITHIUM_3, DILITHIUM_5, FALCON_512, FALCON_1024, SPHINCS_SHA256_128S, SPHINCS_SHA256_128F
        
        If algorithm is not in supported_algorithms:
            Return PqcFailure with:
                error as PqcError.Invalid_Algorithm
                message as "Algorithm not supported: " plus algorithm
        
        Note: Return default parameters if none provided
        Let default_params be dictionary containing:
            "security_level" as security_level,
            "algorithm" as algorithm,
            "validated" as true
        
        If parameters is not None:
            Note: Merge custom parameters with defaults
            For key in keys of parameters:
                Set default_params at key key to parameters at key key
        
        Return PqcSuccess with value as default_params
    
    Catch error:
        Return PqcFailure with:
            error as PqcError.Internal_Error
            message as "Parameter validation error: " plus error as String

Process called "assess_quantum_vulnerability" that takes classical_algorithm as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Assess quantum vulnerability of classical cryptographic algorithm
    Try:
        Let vulnerability_level be "high"
        Let years_until_vulnerable be 10
        Let recommended_pqc_alternative be ""
        
        Match classical_algorithm:
            When "RSA-2048":
                Set vulnerability_level to "critical"
                Set years_until_vulnerable to 5
                Set recommended_pqc_alternative to KYBER_768
            When "RSA-3072":
                Set vulnerability_level to "high" 
                Set years_until_vulnerable to 8
                Set recommended_pqc_alternative to KYBER_1024
            When "ECDSA-P256":
                Set vulnerability_level to "critical"
                Set years_until_vulnerable to 3
                Set recommended_pqc_alternative to DILITHIUM_2
            When "ECDSA-P384":
                Set vulnerability_level to "high"
                Set years_until_vulnerable to 6
                Set recommended_pqc_alternative to DILITHIUM_3
            Otherwise:
                Set vulnerability_level to "unknown"
                Set years_until_vulnerable to 10
                Set recommended_pqc_alternative to KYBER_768
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "vulnerability_level" as vulnerability_level,
            "estimated_years_until_vulnerable" as years_until_vulnerable,
            "recommended_pqc_replacement" as recommended_pqc_alternative,
            "hybrid_transition_recommended" as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "vulnerability_level" as "unknown",
            "estimated_years_until_vulnerable" as 10,
            "recommended_pqc_replacement" as KYBER_768,
            "hybrid_transition_recommended" as true

Process called "determine_hybrid_combination_method" that takes classical_alg as String and pqc_alg as String returns String:
    Note: Determine optimal method for combining classical and PQC algorithms
    Try:
        Note: For signatures, use dual signing
        If pqc_alg contains "Dilithium" or pqc_alg contains "FALCON" or pqc_alg contains "SPHINCS":
            Return "dual_signature"
        
        Note: For KEM, use KEM combination
        If pqc_alg contains "Kyber" or pqc_alg contains "NTRU":
            Return "kem_combination"
        
        Note: Default to parallel execution
        Return "parallel_execution"
    
    Catch error:
        Return "parallel_execution"